RCH0007default&#xa0;default&#xa0;defaultWritten evidence submitted by the defaultChildren’s Services Development Groupdefault&#xa0;defaultThis briefing set
defaults out the views of the Children’s Services Development Group (CSDG) regarding the Government’s planned reforms
default to the regulation of residential children’s homes. It addresses the two questions posed by the Education Select Committee: 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Children’s Services Development Group (CSDG) welcomes the intention of the proposed reforms to the regulation of children’s homes, but is concerned that the narrow focus of the proposed changes will
default not be effective in ensuring that the system protects vulnerable children and acts in their best interests.
default&#xa0;
defaultOur concerns stem from both the exclusive focus on out-of-authority placements in children’s homes, which risks ignoring the majority of vulnerabl
defaulte children, and from the decision to simply increase regulation when care failings are caused by existing regulations not being followed. 
default&#xa0;defaultAbout CSDGdefault&#xa0;
defaultThe Children’s Services Development Group is a policy coalition of leading independent providers of spec
defaultialist services for looked after children and young people with complex needs. Its members
default 
default‒
default Acorn Care &amp; Education, Hesley Group, National Fostering Agency, Options Group,
